# Citation Style Guide

## Overview
This guide provides comprehensive examples for major citation styles used in academic publishing. Always check journal requirements for specific formatting preferences.

## APA Style (7th Edition)

### In-Text Citations
**Parenthetical Citation:**
- (Smith, 2023)
- (Smith & Johnson, 2023)
- (Smith et al., 2023)
- (Smith, 2023, p. 45)

**Narrative Citation:**
- Smith (2023) found that...
- Smith and Johnson (2023) reported...
- Smith et al. (2023) demonstrated...

### Reference List Examples

**Journal Article:**
Smith, J. A., & Johnson, B. K. (2023). Title of the article. *Journal Name, 45*(3), 123-145. https://doi.org/10.1000/abcd123

**Book:**
Johnson, B. K. (2023). *Title of the book* (2nd ed.). Publisher Name. https://doi.org/10.1000/efgh456

**Book Chapter:**
Smith, J. A. (2023). Title of the chapter. In B. K. Johnson (Ed.), *Book title* (pp. 45-67). Publisher Name.

**Website:**
Smith, J. A. (2023, March 15). *Title of webpage*. Website Name. https://www.example.com/page

**Conference Paper:**
Smith, J. A., & Johnson, B. K. (2023, March). Title of paper. *Proceedings of the Conference Name* (pp. 123-145). https://doi.org/10.1000/ijkl789

## MLA Style (9th Edition)

### In-Text Citations
- (Smith 123)
- (Smith and Johnson 123)
- (Smith et al. 123)

### Works Cited Examples

**Journal Article:**
Smith, John A., and Barbara K. Johnson. "Title of the Article." *Journal Name*, vol. 45, no. 3, 2023, pp. 123-45. *JSTOR*, doi:10.1000/abcd123.

**Book:**
Johnson, Barbara K. *Title of the Book*. 2nd ed., Publisher Name, 2023.

**Book Chapter:**
Smith, John A. "Title of the Chapter." *Book Title*, edited by Barbara K. Johnson, Publisher Name, 2023, pp. 45-67.

**Website:**
Smith, John A. "Title of Webpage." *Website Name*, 15 Mar. 2023, www.example.com/page.

## Chicago Style (17th Edition)

### Notes and Bibliography

**Footnote:**
1. John A. Smith and Barbara K. Johnson, "Title of the Article," *Journal Name* 45, no. 3 (2023): 123-45, https://doi.org/10.1000/abcd123.

**Bibliography:**
Smith, John A., and Barbara K. Johnson. "Title of the Article." *Journal Name* 45, no. 3 (2023): 123-45. https://doi.org/10.1000/abcd123.

### Author-Date

**In-Text Citation:**
(Smith and Johnson 2023, 123)

**Reference List:**
Smith, John A., and Barbara K. Johnson. 2023. "Title of the Article." *Journal Name* 45 (3): 123-45. https://doi.org/10.1000/abcd123.

## Vancouver Style

### In-Text Citations
- Numbered superscript: Smith¹
- Numbered in parentheses: (1)

### Reference List Examples

**Journal Article:**
1. Smith JA, Johnson BK. Title of the article. J Name. 2023;45(3):123-45. doi:10.1000/abcd123.

**Book:**
2. Johnson BK. Title of the book. 2nd ed. City: Publisher Name; 2023.

**Book Chapter:**
3. Smith JA. Title of the chapter. In: Johnson BK, editor. Book title. City: Publisher Name; 2023. p. 45-67.

## Harvard Style

### In-Text Citations
- (Smith 2023, p. 45)
- (Smith and Johnson 2023)
- (Smith et al. 2023)

### Reference List Examples

**Journal Article:**
Smith, J.A. and Johnson, B.K. (2023) 'Title of the article', *Journal Name*, 45(3), pp. 123-145. doi: 10.1000/abcd123.

**Book:**
Johnson, B.K. (2023) *Title of the book*. 2nd edn. City: Publisher Name.

## Digital Object Identifiers (DOIs)

### DOI Format
- Always include DOI when available
- Format: https://doi.org/10.1000/abcd123
- Do not use "doi:" prefix in APA 7th edition

### DOI Resolution
- All DOIs should resolve to the correct resource
- Test DOIs before submission
- Use official DOI resolver when in doubt

## Common Citation Elements

### Authors
- List all authors up to the style limit
- Use "et al." when exceeding limits
- Include initials and surnames consistently
- Use institutional authors when appropriate

### Titles
- Use sentence case for article titles (APA, Vancouver)
- Use title case for article titles (MLA, Chicago)
- Italicize journal and book titles
- Include subtitle information

### Publication Information
- Volume numbers in italics
- Issue numbers in parentheses
- Page ranges with full numbers
- Include publisher location when required

## Electronic Sources

### Online Articles
- Include DOI when available
- Include URL when DOI not available
- Include access date for stable URLs
- Note format when applicable

### Databases
- Cite the original source, not the database
- Include database name when required
- Note accession numbers when relevant

### Social Media
- Include author and handle
- Include post date and time
- Include platform name
- Include URL when available

## Special Cases

### Multiple Works by Same Author
- Arrange chronologically
- Use a, b, c for same year
- Include full dates for disambiguation

### Translated Works
- Include original author
- Include translator information
- Include original publication date
- Note translation in citation

### Government Documents
- Use agency as author
- Include report numbers
- Include publication information
- Note series when applicable

## Citation Management Tools

### Recommended Software
- EndNote
- Mendeley
- Zotero
- RefWorks

### Best Practices
- Verify automatic citations
- Update style guides regularly
- Backup citation libraries
- Use consistent formatting

## Avoiding Plagiarism

### Proper Attribution
- Credit all sources used
- Distinguish direct quotes from paraphrases
- Include page numbers for direct quotes
- Cite ideas, not just words

### Common Mistakes
- Incomplete citations
- Missing page numbers
- Incorrect formatting
- Failure to cite all sources

## Journal-Specific Requirements

### Checking Requirements
- Read author guidelines carefully
- Follow specific formatting rules
- Use required citation style
- Include all required elements

### Style Variations
- Journal-specific modifications
- Field-specific conventions
- Regional preferences
- Historical considerations

